com.google.errorprone

Class SuppressionHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.errorprone.SuppressionHelper

  • public class SuppressionHelper
extends Object
    Encapsulates the logic of handling suppressions, both via @SuppressWarnings and via custom suppression annotations. To do this we have to maintains 2 sets of suppression info: 1) A set of the suppression strings in all @Suppresswarnings annotations down this path of the AST. 2) A set of all custom suppression annotations down this path of the AST.

    • Method Detail

      • extendSuppressionSets

        public SuppressionHelper.SuppressionInfo extendSuppressionSets(com.sun.tools.javac.code.Symbol sym,
                                                               com.sun.tools.javac.code.Type suppressWarningsType,
                                                               Set<String> suppressionsOnCurrentPath,
                                                               Set<Class<? extends Annotation>> customSuppressionsOnCurrentPath,
                                                               boolean inGeneratedCode,
                                                               VisitorState state)
        Extend suppression sets for both @SuppressWarnings and custom suppression annotations. When we explore a new node, we have to extend the suppression sets with any new suppressed warnings or custom suppression annotations. We also have to retain the previous suppression set so that we can reinstate it when we move up the tree.

        We do not modify the existing suppression sets, so they can be restored when moving up the tree. We also avoid copying the suppression sets if the next node to explore does not have any suppressed warnings or custom suppression annotations. This is the common case.

        Parameters:
        sym - The Symbol for the AST node currently being scanned
        suppressWarningsType - The Type for @SuppressWarnings, as given by javac's symbol table
        suppressionsOnCurrentPath - The set of strings in all @SuppressWarnings annotations on the current path through the AST
        customSuppressionsOnCurrentPath - The set of all custom suppression annotations
